"use strict";(self.webpackChunkpos_doc=self.webpackChunkpos_doc||[]).push([[972],{5358(t,e,i){i.r(e),i.d(e,{_pageData:()=>o,default:()=>a});var s=i(641);const o=JSON.parse('{"path":"/guide/stock-visibility.html","title":"Stock Visibility Controls","lang":"en-US","frontmatter":{"title":"Stock Visibility Controls","description":"Control stock level visibility in WooCommerce POS from admin settings and register display toggles."},"git":{},"filePathRelative":"guide/stock-visibility.md"}'),n={name:"stock-visibility.md"},a=(0,i(6262).A)(n,[["render",function(t,e,i,o,n,a){return(0,s.uX)(),(0,s.CE)("div",null,[...e[0]||(e[0]=[(0,s.Fv)('<h1 id="stock-visibility-controls" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#stock-visibility-controls"><span>Stock Visibility Controls</span></a></h1><h2 id="introduction" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#introduction"><span>Introduction</span></a></h2><p>Real-time inventory visibility helps cashiers manage checkout workflows without risking overselling or cashier confusion. WooCommerce Point of Sale (POS) includes flexible <strong>Stock Visibility Controls</strong> that let store administrators choose whether active stock counts are displayed on product catalog tiles or hidden completely.</p><p>This page explains how to configure stock visibility from the admin backend and details how these settings change the cashier experience in the POS register.</p><hr><h2 id="configuration-workflow" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#configuration-workflow"><span>Configuration Workflow</span></a></h2><h3 id="_1-display-stock-setting-enabled" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#_1-display-stock-setting-enabled"><span>1. Display Stock Setting Enabled</span></a></h3><p>To show product stock quantities in the POS terminal, administrators must first enable the display settings within the WordPress admin dashboard:</p><ol><li>Log in to the WordPress Admin Panel.</li><li>Navigate to <strong>Point of Sale</strong> &gt; <strong>Settings</strong> &gt; <strong>Other Settings</strong>.</li><li>Locate the <strong>Display Stock</strong> toggle.</li><li>Set the toggle to <strong>Enabled</strong> (or checked).</li><li>Save the configuration settings.</li></ol><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/displaystockenable.webp" alt="Display Stock Setting Enabled"></p><hr><h3 id="_2-stock-visible-in-pos" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#_2-stock-visible-in-pos"><span>2. Stock Visible in POS</span></a></h3><p>Once the display stock setting is enabled, the active inventory numbers sync directly to the terminal interface.</p><p>POS cashiers will see the exact remaining stock levels printed on each product tile in the catalog grid (e.g., &quot;10 In Stock&quot;). This gives them real-time info on what is left in the warehouse or store floor.</p><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/enabledstocks.webp" alt="Stock Visible in POS"></p><hr><h3 id="_3-display-stock-setting-disabled" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#_3-display-stock-setting-disabled"><span>3. Display Stock Setting Disabled</span></a></h3><p>If you want to hide stock counts from terminal agents to maintain a cleaner design or prevent customer visibility, the setting can be deactivated:</p><ol><li>Log in to the WordPress Admin Panel.</li><li>Navigate to <strong>Point of Sale</strong> &gt; <strong>Settings</strong> &gt; <strong>Other Settings</strong>.</li><li>Toggle the <strong>Display Stock</strong> field to <strong>Disabled</strong> (or unchecked).</li><li>Save the configuration settings.</li></ol><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/displaystockdisable.webp" alt="Display Stock Setting Disabled"></p><hr><h3 id="_4-stock-hidden-in-pos" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#_4-stock-hidden-in-pos"><span>4. Stock Hidden in POS</span></a></h3><p>When the display stock setting is disabled, the system suppresses all numeric counts in the register interface.</p><p>The product tiles on the POS catalog grid will no longer show any remaining quantity numbers. This is ideal for stores that do not want checkout agents to focus on stock levels or for service-based businesses.</p><p><img src="/pos-for-woocommerce/images/woocommerce-pos/disabledstocks.webp" alt="Stock Hidden in POS"></p><hr><h2 id="visibility-modes-comparison" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#visibility-modes-comparison"><span>Visibility Modes Comparison</span></a></h2><p>The table below contrasts the difference between enabled and disabled stock visibility configurations:</p><table><thead><tr><th style="text-align:left;">Feature/Metric</th><th style="text-align:left;">Display Stock Enabled</th><th style="text-align:left;">Display Stock Disabled</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style="text-align:left;"><strong>Grid Presentation</strong></td><td style="text-align:left;">Shows exact numeric quantity on each product tile (e.g., &quot;15 left&quot;).</td><td style="text-align:left;">Displays product titles and prices with no stock counts.</td></tr><tr><td style="text-align:left;"><strong>Cashier Focus</strong></td><td style="text-align:left;">Ideal for inventory-centric sales, alerting cashiers to low stock.</td><td style="text-align:left;">Focuses strictly on rapid barcode scanning and item selection.</td></tr><tr><td style="text-align:left;"><strong>Customer Discretion</strong></td><td style="text-align:left;">Visible to customers standing near the register screen.</td><td style="text-align:left;">Keeps specific warehouse stock levels confidential.</td></tr><tr><td style="text-align:left;"><strong>Checkout Behavior</strong></td><td style="text-align:left;">Cashiers can visually confirm availability before adding to cart.</td><td style="text-align:left;">Rely on system warnings at the cart phase if an item is out of stock.</td></tr></tbody></table><hr><h2 id="related-features" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#related-features"><span>Related Features</span></a></h2><ul><li><a href="/woocommerce-pos/products-inventory" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Inventory &amp; Products Management</a> — Set up multi-location stock levels and sync settings.</li><li><a href="/woocommerce-pos/features" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Key System Features</a> — Understand how the offline engine handles cached inventory listings.</li></ul>',32)])])}]])}}]);